534
00:29:49,373 --> 00:29:51,173
Marty will not be paying
for a trip to Mexico.

535
00:29:51,250 --> 00:29:52,290
[DEBORAH] But he promised.

536
00:29:52,334 --> 00:29:54,729
[IKE] Any promise Marty made
was made verbally and not in writing.

537
00:29:54,753 --> 00:29:59,151
- Who gives a shit?
- It was also made in good faith, assuming the relationship was ongoing.

538
00:29:59,216 --> 00:30:00,860
- No, he never said anything about that.
- No, he never said anything about that.

539
00:30:00,884 --> 00:30:04,555
I said I'd always wanted to go to Mexico,
and Marty said he would pay. Marty?

540
00:30:04,638 --> 00:30:06,348
You said you would pay. Right?

541
00:30:09,434 --> 00:30:11,854
- Are you trying to take advantage of him?
- No.

542
00:30:11,937 --> 00:30:13,313
It sounds like you are.

543
00:30:13,397 --> 00:30:15,157
Do you really want to be
that kind of person?

544
00:30:15,232 --> 00:30:16,942
No. He said.

545
00:30:17,776 --> 00:30:18,819
Marty, tell him.

546
00:30:18,902 --> 00:30:21,154
You said it. You said that you would pay.

547
00:30:21,238 --> 00:30:25,367
[IKE] I can't speak to
what he said before, but I can hear quite clearly what he's saying now.

548
00:30:25,450 --> 00:30:27,327
And what he's saying is, "no more."

549
00:30:28,287 --> 00:30:36,420
Marty says you are to cease
and desist from calling, from coming to his workplace, and from any and all contact from him or with any member of his family.

550
00:30:37,629 --> 00:30:43,343
Marty also says if you do not cease
and desist, he will not hesitate to use the full force of the law against you.

551
00:30:43,427 --> 00:30:46,763
Marty says he will not be paying
for a trip to Mexico.

552
00:30:46,847 --> 00:30:57,552
- Not today, not tomorrow, not ever.
- [DEBORAH GASPS] Marty also says, if you continue in this vein, - the only view your room will have is a view of the prison yard. - The only view your room will have is a view of the prison yard.

553
00:31:00,861 --> 00:31:01,862
Martin.

554
00:31:03,113 --> 00:31:04,239
Did you say that?

555
00:31:05,741 --> 00:31:07,993
I said something very much to that effect.

556
00:31:10,454 --> 00:31:11,914
This meeting has been documented.

557
00:31:12,873 --> 00:31:13,874
Good day.

558
00:31:13,957 --> 00:31:16,835
It has been documented, so… Get out of my apartment.

559
00:31:20,297 --> 00:31:23,133
- [LAUGHS, WHEEZES]
- Oh! [CHUCKLES] Oh, my God.

560
00:31:23,217 --> 00:31:25,761
- Did you see her face?
- I feel like I'm on drugs.

561
00:31:25,844 --> 00:31:29,640
I mean, I've never taken them before, but, I mean, I assume this is what drugs feel like.

562
00:31:29,723 --> 00:31:31,683
- You feel good?
- I feel amazing.

563
00:31:31,767 --> 00:31:33,685
Wait, "view of the prison yard"?

564
00:31:33,769 --> 00:31:36,021
- [LAUGHS]
- That was a stroke of genius.

565
00:31:36,104 --> 00:31:38,398
- It was, wasn't it? Give me five.
- Yeah. [CLAPS]

566
00:31:38,482 --> 00:31:40,025
- Give me ten.
- Yeah. [CLAPS]

567
00:31:40,108 --> 00:31:41,669
- Give me seven and a half.
